  "local_port": 41658,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best Hindi songs to sing?",
  "response": "Singing Hindi songs can be a delightful experience, whether you're performing for an audience or just enjoying a personal moment. Here's a list of some of the best Hindi songs that are popular and loved by many, suitable for various singing levels:\n\n### For Beginners:\n1. **\"Tum Hi Ho\" - Aashiqui 2**\n   - Sung by: Arijit Singh\n   - This romantic ballad has a simple melody and lyrics, making it easier for beginners to learn.\n\n2. **\"Chura Liya Hai Tumne Jo Dil Ko\" - Yaadon Ki Baaraat**\n   - Sung by: Asha Bhosle and Mohammed Rafi\n   - A timeless classic with a memorable tune that is relatively easy to sing.\n\n3. **\"Kabira\" - Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani**\n   - Sung by: Rekha Bhardwaj and Tochi Raina\n   - A popular song with a soothing melody that is great for practicing singing technique.\n\n### For Intermediate Singers:\n1. **\"Agar Tum Saath Ho\" - Tamasha**\n   - Sung by: Alka Yagnik and Arijit Singh\n   - An emotional song with a challenging range, perfect for intermediate singers to work on their vocal control.\n\n2. **\"Tujhe Kitna Chahne Lage\" - Kabir Singh**\n   - Sung by: Arijit Singh\n   - A beautiful melody with heartfelt lyrics, this song requires some practice but is rewarding to sing.\n\n3. **\"Ae Dil Hai Mushkil\" - Ae Dil Hai Mushkil**\n   - Sung by: Arijit Singh\n   - This song has a wide vocal range and emotional depth, making it a good challenge for intermediate singers.\n\n### For Advanced Singers:\n1. **\"Tera Ban Jaunga\" - Kabir Singh**\n   - Sung by: Tulsi Kumar and Arijit Singh\n   - A complex and emotional duet that showcases the singers' skills and range.\n\n2. **\"Channa Mereya\" - Ae Dil Hai Mushkil**\n   - Sung by: Arijit Singh\n   - An intense and soulful song that requires strong vocal control and emotional expression.\n\n3. **\"Tere Bina\" - Guru**\n   - Sung by: A.R. Rahman, Murtuza Khan, Qadir Khan, and Chinmayee\n   - A challenging song with a haunting melody and intricate lyrics, suitable for advanced singers.\n\n### Evergreen Classics:\n1. **\"Lag Jaa Gale\" - Woh Kaun Thi?**\n   - Sung by: Lata Mangeshkar\n   - A beautiful and melancholic song that never goes out of style.\n\n2. **\"Pyaar Kiya To Darna Kya\" - Mughal-E-Azam**\n   - Sung by: Lata Mangeshkar\n   - A classic that requires a good understanding of classical music elements.\n\n3. **\"Yeh Raat Bheegi Bheegi\" - Chori Chori**\n   - Sung by: Kishore Kumar and Lata Mangeshkar\n   - A romantic duet with lovely melody and lyrics, perfect for those who enjoy singing duets.\n\nRemember, the key to singing well is practice and understanding the emotion behind the song. Choose songs that you feel connected to, and don't hesitate to experiment with different genres and styles!",
